  "prompt": "Why did my guy friend ask me if I have a boyfriend or not?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why your guy friend might have asked if you have a boyfriend. Here are some of the most common possibilities:\n\n**1. He's interested in you romantically.** This is the most common and often assumed reason. He might be testing the waters to see if you're available. Knowing your relationship status helps him gauge his chances and decide whether or not to pursue you further.\n\n*   **Signs that this might be the reason:** He's been acting differently around you lately, initiating more conversations, being more attentive, complimenting you, or finding reasons to spend time with you.\n\n**2. He's just curious.** It could be a casual question asked out of general interest in your life. People often ask about relationships as a standard part of getting to know someone.\n\n*   **Signs that this might be the reason:** He asked the question casually, without dwelling on the answer, and moved on to other topics quickly.\n\n**3. He's trying to set you up with someone.** He might have a friend he thinks you'd be a good match with and wanted to know if you were single.\n\n*   **Signs that this might be the reason:** He follows up by asking about your dating preferences, or mentions a friend he thinks you'd like.\n\n**4. He needs a plus-one for an event.** He might be invited to a wedding, party, or other event that requires a date, and he was considering asking you if you were available.\n\n*   **Signs that this might be the reason:** He mentions an event soon after asking about your relationship status.\n\n**5. He's being a supportive friend.** He might be genuinely concerned about your well-being and want to know if you're happy and fulfilled in your romantic life (or lack thereof).\n\n*   **Signs that this might be the reason:** He's always been a caring and supportive friend, and the question feels like it comes from a place of genuine concern.\n\n**6. He's comparing his relationship status to yours.** Maybe he's recently single, in a relationship, or just thinking about his own love life and is curious about yours in comparison.\n\n**7. It was part of a broader conversation about relationships.** Perhaps you were talking about a mutual friend's relationship, and the topic naturally shifted to your own.\n\n**How to figure out the real reason:**\n\n*   **Consider his behavior:** Has he been acting differently around you lately?\n*   **Look at the context:** What were you talking about before he asked the question?\n*   **Pay attention to his reaction:** How did he respond to your answer? Did he seem relieved, disappointed, or just neutral?\n*   **Don't be afraid to ask (indirectly):** If you're comfortable, you could subtly ask him why he was curious.  For example, \"Why do you ask?\" or \"That's a random question! What made you think of that?\"\n\nUltimately, the best way to know for sure is to observe his behavior and consider the context of the conversation. You could even ask him directly, but that depends on your comfort level and the nature of your friendship. Good luck!\n",
